content: Hello,RT!You made the great effort work for very a long time,I admire you !
As a result of our changes, we will have the Analyses Department lessons on Saturdays from now on,
and the Theory Department will go to sleep for some time.
As you know, next year in May, the renju opening rules will change,
therefore it is wise to wait for changes,
and then update our theory according to new changes.
yes. Then old theory will become useless ???
Thank you all for coming here today!
As the the Analyses lessons will be on Saturdays, it is also more suitable with my schedule.
and to YKS, the old theory will not become useless.
Whatever the new rule will be, the change will be small. So all the old theory will still be useful.
So, I remind once more: Until next year's May, the Theory Department will be closed,
and the Analyses Department will have lessons on Saturdays.
u may find new rule by yourself
Today I will teach the lesson.
Today is the 4th part of the World Championship games,
Previously, I had told you about first 8 rounds of WC.
The situation after 8 rounds was really exciting - both Sushkov and I had 6 points.
if u want to speak chinese ,maybe after our class
And he had better coefficient, in case of equal points in the end of the tournament.
So I had to get at least half point lead.
I played the 9th round with Hermansson
Yes, I opened d11, because I was sure Hermansson does not know the details of that opening well, in that particular variant.
Mr. Sushkov got 2rd place thr times in WC AT.

slamduk, oddgod, yaya, lkogr, minuta, ice, voshkod, yuelee00, slappanu, lq20008, xinxin, YKS, dongfujia, whte, tianxia, skywalker, Torsten, weigui, Shangjin, dein, StarRain, Fermat, shuwang, LiuJianping.
As I tought, he did not swap,
so I chose this plan for black.
YKS, its not easy to say which is better.
The theory of 13-h10 is changing a lot these days.
Some months ago, the theory of h10 was considered so good for black,
then WC showed some good ways for white there,
i believe black maybe better now
sometimes good for black, sometimes good for white.
Yes, I chose h10, for the good reason.
h10 gives more complicated variant than j9.
And I had a good reason to believe,
that he will not play the best moves there.
In renju game, we dont need to play absolute best moves,
Those who had seen some latest tournament games before WC,
and also the WC first rounds games,
had made some conclusions about good and bad moves here.
Maybe you remember my game with Tunnet,
How about this 21, do you know win?
Just before that game, I had told Chingin about my game with Purk,
and I told, that I had prepared such tactics with 4x4 control,
The stone 22, gives a chance to make a threat by move 30,
so the optimal black plan is to go to k9 without i12,
so that white will not get that threat at m10
seems so.  21st doesn't help at all.
This is how our game continued.
The situation after 25th move is very complicated.
I think its quite equal position
both black and white have chance here.
But if the player does not understand the deep ideas of this variant,
he may easily choose the wrong tactics.
In this situation seems that black has no attack.
if black doesnt attack, then white can attack.
because white's position is not mature for attacking,
while black has a small advantage in most of areas of the board.
He played such an active move.
As you know, whatever move on left upper side,
black would respond to i12 or some other defense anyway,
and as a result, the f9 stone becomes a waste -
and its defense power is nearly nothing
the line 7_1 is open for black,
the line from 25 to bottow is open too
So you can see that stone 26 is so meaningless defemse,
and now, after these natural 27 and 29, white has to defend.
it pushes blacks further into corner,
and breaks the diagonal connection to stone 29.
or hoping to imitate a fake attack,
in order to fill up the space.
I had to continue development of attack,
and same time, had to reduce his defense power.
those white pairs might annoy blacks a lot in later game.
I began the most natural attack now.
But he was able to find the defense!
it cuts my e12 with a three at h15
you won against hannes,, so the answer must be yes.....
in the game, i spent much time on search
I was under big pressure by then.
I saw that I dont have win,
and same time, it let me realize that if the game would end with a draw,
maybe try to build in another area first to kill som activity
it would reduce my chances to first place.
Whenever you see that its not possible to win,
dont try to cheat the opponent with some simple attack,
because if he does all right, then your position will get much worse.
The early "exit" from corner can still be hopeful
At some point, we were both in time trouble,
especially, in the end, it was really a nervous situation.
Now I attacked in the bottom.
I was so tired from all tournament already,
so I saw some fake wins already.
After opponent's 52, i began to think about 53-m11
It seems to wim for black.
but then i looked at bottom,
and realized, its simple win there
I was so blinded, i thought, after j4 i have vcf
you know, every player gets blinded sometimes,
especially after long and tired tournament
of course there is no win, simple cut
The crowd was around the table at that time,
I am sure they were all so confused and surprised
wondering what I was doing there
But then I took a deep breath, and calmed myself,
The idea of k6 was just to clear up my silly mistake at the bottom,
and get rid of the white line
I did not need the bottom area any more
so the 57 was just a safe "exit" again
and here, i had much pressure,
because the time was running fast
yes, maybe he could have tried different 60,
Who wants to show black win here,
In the game, I has also a little trap
if you had not played 49-57, then maybe easy.
here, i thought, if he is careless,
seems like a good white move
so I didnt have the chance to try this trap
At the same time, Sushkov made draw with Okabe,
and I got half point lead.
It was quite fine for me.
The 10th round - the most decisive match,
4 years ago, in WC in Kyoto, I played this variant with Ants as white.
skywalker, whte, voshkod, oddgod, YKS, Fermat, slappanu, lkogr, ice, StarRain, LiuJianping, Torsten, minuta, dein, dongfujia, lq20008, yaya, slamduk, tianxia, yuelee00, Shangjin, weigui, xinxin.
Do you know my 20th move at that time?
I tried to break away from traditional soft style,
I could not find good move
After long thinking, i found the best 21!
And then it was his turn to think deeply for a long time.
both sides must make deep counting
he wanted the K5 point very much,
After 26, I looked at the position,
I was so tired of all games, my mind was not bright,
and I started to count VCT at the top,
then i go m8 and m7 to block it,
then if he stops it near, i win, if far, then.... who knows!
its not a good sign of a top player
but i was really tired by then.
And he blocks it with only move.
and this is the situation, which was inevitable,
When I looked at the outcome, I felt regret for attacking so straight.
It would have been wiser to try softer 27 at the bottom, forcing him to defend,
and then get another stone at bottom left,
with decent black advantage for the rest of the game
But now, I realized, I did not only lose my win chance,
but also i lost the positional control.
So from that moment, I understood, I cannot win this game any more, and I might need to fight hard, to bring a draw.
Luckily i was not too crazy to continue attacking :P
I calmed down, and made a plan, how to use all power for defense.
Now I had stretched the upper side a bit.
It was necessary in order to catch 1 more tempo later.
He could not continue attack on the left side now.
Because whatever move he would make,
so I could respond at the top,
and give him trouble by that.
and extremely active for white self.
but great 53 and 55 - they took the maximum of black's energy,
to break the inner power of whites.
nobody wants to take g11 point.
Because whoever takes it, weakens his own position.
I kept around 5 minutes on my clock all the time,
in order to avoid the time trouble mistake, which I made with Karlsson before.
I had to play with Tarannikov.
He does not even hope to win.
And draw for me would mean 2nd place.
It is hard to win against the player who only wishes draw.
I knew he would open d11,
So I was forced to do the most unusual thing for me,
I was better prepared this time.
I had prepared many hours at night.
I knew he would go g6,
because a draw-monster would always go g6
And I also knew he got help from Sushkov and Chingin last night,
so I had to change something.
i played a bit strange move.
And then, he acted as being hypnotized.
With a few moments of thinking,
he had prepared for many moves,
but he mixed up the variant.
because a player who only focuses on memory archive, without looking on board,
Anyway, it would have been an interesting fight,
I think black has more good points than white.
With that game, I got the 8.5 points,
White must be draw at best.
Thank you all for joining the lesson.
And sorry about the delay at the start, due to absence of GM.
And next lesson is on Saturday (not Tuesday).
Homework will be available later today.
